1
00:00:03,003 --> 00:00:07,132
(Toshie) Huh? An attorney representing the defendant in a claim for damages?

2
00:00:07,215 --> 00:00:09,676
(Rie) Huh? Charge amount...

3
00:00:10,260 --> 00:00:11,302
100 million yen! ?

4
00:00:15,015 --> 00:00:16,224
(Rie) Please

5
00:00:18,184 --> 00:00:20,895
This is Reiko Seyama.

6
00:00:21,813 --> 00:00:23,106
I go there⸺

7
00:00:23,857 --> 00:00:26,526
Meigo, a friend of mine from the voice training class

8
00:00:27,444 --> 00:00:29,279
(Kotaro) You work at a cleaning company.

9
00:00:29,362 --> 00:00:30,321
(Reiko) Yes.

10
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:35,493
(Torataro) Is the plaintiff who sued Mr. Seyama Professor Kurashiki of Eio University?

11
00:00:35,577 --> 00:00:37,370
Why was he sued⸺

12
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:38,997
Would you like to talk to me?

13
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:43,543
the…

14
00:00:45,128 --> 00:00:47,922
Cleaning Professor Kurashiki's laboratory⸺

15
00:00:48,006 --> 00:00:50,175
Our company is contracting it⸺

16
00:00:51,051 --> 00:00:54,220
This is where slime molds and other organisms can be cultivated for a long period of time.

17
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:56,431
I have a heating device⸺

18
00:00:56,514 --> 00:01:01,519
On the 20th of last month, I was doing my cleaning work as usual⸺

19
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:04,647
The outlet I usually use is blocked.

20
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:06,357
(Kawamoto) I'm busy, so finish it quickly.

21
00:01:06,441 --> 00:01:08,943
Sorry yes

22
00:01:12,697 --> 00:01:17,202
The plug I pulled out belonged to that heating device.

23
00:01:19,162 --> 00:01:22,874
(Toratarō) I unplugged the power to the heating device during the experiment.

24
00:01:22,957 --> 00:01:25,794
(Rie) Maybe that's why Nenkin-kun died?

25
00:01:28,463 --> 00:01:32,759
It seems that the experiment that I have been conducting for many years has been ruined.

26
00:01:32,842 --> 00:01:35,762
(Torataro) So the laboratory asked for compensation?

27
00:01:36,554 --> 00:01:40,725
The amount of damage is said to be as much as 100 million yen.

28
00:01:40,809 --> 00:01:42,227
Everyone gather

29
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:45,063
- (Torataro) Yes - (Tatsumi) Yes

30
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:50,819
100 million yen. 100 million yen. What do you think?

31
00:01:50,902 --> 00:01:53,613
(Tatsumi) Even if you add the prize money from the Ryuo match and the Meijin match, it won't arrive.

32
00:01:53,696 --> 00:01:55,281
Shogi is good

33
00:01:55,365 --> 00:01:58,451
If it is determined that the client was 100% at fault⸺

34
00:01:58,535 --> 00:02:00,495
I have to pay exactly like that.

35
00:02:00,578 --> 00:02:04,332
Isn't it obvious that this is going to be a tough battle?

36
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:05,750
A tough battle...

37
00:02:05,834 --> 00:02:07,669
(Rie) This is about Mr. Yoshida who introduced me⸺

38
00:02:07,752 --> 00:02:10,004
It seems like she hasn't asked any other agencies at all.

39
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:12,757
I guess you were planning on going to trial without a lawyer?

40
00:02:12,841 --> 00:02:15,093
I'm already in trouble because I'm carrying it all by myself⸺

41
00:02:15,176 --> 00:02:16,719
I was asked to do something...

42
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:17,846
Understood

43
00:02:18,847 --> 00:02:21,474
We will accept this request.

44
00:02:22,058 --> 00:02:23,434
Wait, why are you accepting this without permission?

45
00:02:23,518 --> 00:02:25,854
Even if it's a tough battle⸺

46
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:28,398
A game where the winner or loser is decided even before you make a move!

47
00:02:28,481 --> 00:02:30,191
Not a single game

48
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:35,947
Since I accept the offer, I will do my best to help you win.

49
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:41,536
thank you

50
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:47,834
♪～

51
00:02:57,886 --> 00:02:59,888
～♪

52
00:02:59,971 --> 00:03:04,142
This is the Kurashiki Laboratory of the Department of Biology.

53
00:03:04,225 --> 00:03:06,269
Professor Kurashiki here⸺

54
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:08,688
Globally groundbreaking experiment⸺

55
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:10,356
It means that it is being done.

56
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,274
 (Kurashiki) Yes

57
00:03:11,357 --> 00:03:13,943
What is being cultured in this insulating device⸺

58
00:03:14,027 --> 00:03:15,737
A special slime mold

59
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:16,863
 (Kawamoto) What is slime mold?

60
00:03:16,946 --> 00:03:18,865
What is it?

61
00:03:18,948 --> 00:03:20,658
(Kurashiki) Slime mold is an example⸺

62
00:03:20,742 --> 00:03:22,952
It also exists in the soil of this campus.

63
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:24,204
For us⸺

64
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:26,247
It's a very familiar life form.

65
00:03:26,331 --> 00:03:27,916
Short life cycle⸺

66
00:03:27,999 --> 00:03:29,250
Simple differentiation

67
00:03:29,334 --> 00:03:30,960
Handling and training⸺

68
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:32,378
Known for being easy

69
00:03:32,462 --> 00:03:33,880
University PR video⸺

70
00:03:33,963 --> 00:03:35,548
What does it mean to be featured?

71
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:37,884
It seems like it was groundbreaking research.

72
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:39,552
What I am researching is⸺

73
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:41,512
A very special slime mold

74
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:42,805
Well, for humanity⸺

75
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:46,267
It has the potential to create unknown antibiotics

76
00:03:46,351 --> 00:03:48,478
But the problem is⸺

77
00:03:48,561 --> 00:03:51,147
Because it is an extremely delicate slime mold⸺

78
00:03:51,230 --> 00:03:54,067
After 20 years⸺

79
00:03:54,150 --> 00:03:56,194
So we need to keep an eye on it.

80
00:03:56,277 --> 00:03:57,320
(sound of key press)

81
00:03:57,820 --> 00:04:01,157
(Rie) Hmm, if an unknown antibiotic is discovered⸺

82
00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:03,743
It can also be used as a treatment for intractable diseases⸺

83
00:04:03,826 --> 00:04:06,246
If you get a patent, you will make a huge profit.

84
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:07,705
(Torataro) Yeah.

85
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:10,458
However, according to the complaint, 100 million yen is...

86
00:04:10,541 --> 00:04:12,418
I would have gotten it in the future⸺

87
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:14,796
Not lost profits⸺

88
00:04:14,879 --> 00:04:18,341
It looks like the total amount invested in research so far.

89
00:04:18,424 --> 00:04:23,096
Approximately 100 million yen over 18 years at 6 million yen per year

90
00:04:23,179 --> 00:04:24,013
(Torataro) Yeah.

91
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:26,182
(Rie) But what's strange is⸺

92
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:29,185
Mr. Seyama is an employee of a cleaning company⸺

93
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:31,521
According to the complaint, Mr. Seyama is the only defendant.

94
00:04:31,604 --> 00:04:33,648
The company usually sue, right?

95
00:04:33,731 --> 00:04:37,402
You'll save more money that way, and you're more likely to have insurance.

96
00:04:37,485 --> 00:04:40,655
Yes, if the cleaning company has liability insurance⸺

97
00:04:40,738 --> 00:04:45,243
Mr. Seyama may not have to pay the entire 100 million yen.

98
00:04:45,910 --> 00:04:47,787
(Torataro) I don't have insurance! ?

99
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:50,248
 (Iguchi) Of course, there are injuries to employees⸺

100
00:04:50,331 --> 00:04:53,251
I was prepared for an accident.

101
00:04:53,793 --> 00:04:55,878
I unplugged the power⸺

102
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:58,756
In case the other party's business goes bad⸺

103
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:01,217
What kind of insurance covers it⸺

104
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:04,095
As expected, it's not included.

105
00:05:04,178 --> 00:05:05,221
(Tatsumi) Even if...

106
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:06,973
Reiko Seyama is an employee, so to speak.

107
00:05:07,056 --> 00:05:07,890
centre?

108
00:05:07,974 --> 00:05:10,184
(Tatsumi) If Ayumu's negligence causes damage to a third party⸺

109
00:05:10,268 --> 00:05:13,396
The user, that is, the company that owns the ball, bears most of the responsibility.

110
00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:14,564
This is the general tendency of courts

111
00:05:14,647 --> 00:05:15,481
(Iguchi) Gyoku?

112
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:17,859
(Torataro) Trials and shogi are mixed together again.

113
00:05:17,942 --> 00:05:18,860
(Tatsumi) Oh, sorry.

114
00:05:18,943 --> 00:05:21,529
(Torataro) Originally, this company and President Iguchi were the ones responsible.

115
00:05:21,612 --> 00:05:24,574
I'm supposed to be eligible for compensation...

116
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:26,200
That was Mr. Seyama⸺

117
00:05:26,284 --> 00:05:29,203
You said you'd do something by yourself.

118
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:33,583
(Reiko) It's all my fault for pulling the plug.

119
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:36,377
We will not cause any inconvenience to the company.

120
00:05:36,461 --> 00:05:37,962
(Torataro) That’s it⸺

121
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:40,673
Mr. Seyama also covers the company's bills⸺

122
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:42,884
Does that mean negotiating with the plaintiff?

123
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:47,805
(Iguchi) I don't really understand, but that's what I told the lawyer over there.

124
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:50,558
In the first place, the cleaning of that laboratory was...

125
00:05:50,641 --> 00:05:55,313
She said she was willing to take it on herself.

126
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:58,191
I accepted it from myself...

127
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:00,026
(Rie) I see.

128
00:06:00,109 --> 00:06:02,737
So Mr. Seyama was the only defendant.

129
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:06,491
What's more, the plaintiff is neither Eio University nor the Faculty of Science⸺

130
00:06:06,574 --> 00:06:08,534
Professor Kurashiki personally

131
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:11,537
According to the reputation on the internet, Kurashiki is a professor⸺

132
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:14,707
He seems so bullish and proud.

133
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:16,793
Maybe he took the initiative to appeal.

134
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:18,252
(sigh)

135
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:25,343
I can't believe you're calling me an anaguma again...

136
00:06:25,426 --> 00:06:29,555
(Tatsumi) Ah, no, this time I can't use the same fixed mark as before.

137
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:32,475
Last time, I was the plaintiff and the complainant⸺

138
00:06:32,558 --> 00:06:36,187
This time, I am representing the defendant who is being sued...

139
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:39,357
I'm on the draw.

140
00:06:41,109 --> 00:06:43,820
Does being behind the pack mean you're at a disadvantage?

141
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:47,573
(Tatsumi) No, there are strategies for being on the defensive.

142
00:06:47,657 --> 00:06:53,037
Mr. Kurashiki is not only a professor at a famous university, but also a plaintiff himself.

143
00:06:53,121 --> 00:06:53,955
As a researcher⸺

144
00:06:54,038 --> 00:06:56,791
The type of battle chosen by people who want to take the initiative is⸺

145
00:06:56,874 --> 00:06:59,043
Straight rook (Ibisha)

146
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:06,092
The rook is the rook⸺

147
00:07:06,175 --> 00:07:09,387
It is a tactic of fighting without moving from two fixed positions.

148
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:12,390
Our strategy on the defensive is⸺

149
00:07:12,473 --> 00:07:16,352
Of course Gokigen Chuubisha

150
00:07:18,771 --> 00:07:20,648
I don't know which is obvious though

151
00:07:20,731 --> 00:07:23,109
Gokigennakavisha? That sounds like a fun name

152
00:07:23,192 --> 00:07:25,653
(Tatsumi) Place the rook in front of the opponent's ball⸺

153
00:07:25,736 --> 00:07:27,613
It is characterized by swinging in 5 lines.

154
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:30,116
(Rie) Ah, I'll put the rook in the middle, so it's the middle rook.

155
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:31,617
Ah... that's instructive.

156
00:07:31,701 --> 00:07:34,078
This is a law firm, not a shogi dojo.

157
00:07:34,162 --> 00:07:37,165
Even if you are the defendant, you cannot win by focusing solely on defense.

158
00:07:37,248 --> 00:07:39,375
You can attack aggressively even on the draw⸺

159
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:42,378
Gokigen Chuubisha is the one who can aim for the counter⸺

160
00:07:42,461 --> 00:07:45,256
This can be said to be the best evidence for this trial.

161
00:07:45,339 --> 00:07:46,883
(phone ringtone)

162
00:07:47,925 --> 00:07:49,802
Yes, I'm always smiling and laughing at Chuubisha⸺

163
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:51,762
This is Fuda Law Office.

164
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:56,142
Ah, Mr. Yamaoka, yes, uh... the plaintiff's attorney.

165
00:07:58,394 --> 00:07:59,604
Settlement agreement! ?

166
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:15,661
Um... what are the terms of the settlement?

167
00:08:15,745 --> 00:08:20,082
(Yamaoka) It would be impossible to pay 100 million yen due to the defendant's financial situation!

168
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:22,460
The defendant admitted 100% fault⸺

169
00:08:22,543 --> 00:08:23,711
Submit it to the university⸺

170
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:26,297
I hope you will also apologize to the plaintiff.

171
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:30,760
Compensation may be reduced to an amount that can be paid...

172
00:08:30,843 --> 00:08:32,303
Yes, is it possible?

173
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:39,185
(Torataro) I wonder if it's a reduction... It seems like quite an extraordinary condition.

174
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:43,022
(Tatsumi) They have filed a lawsuit, and the first deadline has not yet been met⸺

175
00:08:43,105 --> 00:08:45,149
Why such a proposal for reconciliation?

176
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:50,029
Well, at first the experiment was ruined⸺

177
00:08:50,112 --> 00:08:53,199
I filed a lawsuit out of anger.

178
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:57,578
Well, if you think about it calmly, what is important for us researchers is⸺

179
00:08:57,662 --> 00:08:59,789
It's not about regretting your failures.

180
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:05,044
It's about taking a step forward for the future of humanity.

181
00:09:05,127 --> 00:09:07,713
That's the conclusion I came to.

182
00:09:07,797 --> 00:09:12,134
Besides, I wonder if it would be better for Seyama-kun too.

183
00:09:13,177 --> 00:09:14,512
Understood

184
00:09:14,595 --> 00:09:16,556
I will consider taking it home for now.

185
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:17,890
Excuse me

186
00:09:20,434 --> 00:09:22,520
(Torataro) Alright, alright, alright!

187
00:09:22,603 --> 00:09:25,773
What if the compensation amount goes down to 30 million or even 20 million?

188
00:09:25,856 --> 00:09:28,317
I'm sure Mr. Seyama will agree!

189
00:09:29,193 --> 00:09:32,738
Huh? Mr. Ryumi...

190
00:09:32,822 --> 00:09:34,824
(Student) Aren't you a lawyer?

191
00:09:36,784 --> 00:09:39,704
(Torataro) Wait... what are you doing already?

192
00:09:39,787 --> 00:09:40,955
Sorry, I was going to the library.

193
00:09:41,038 --> 00:09:41,872
(Torataro) Huh?

194
00:09:41,956 --> 00:09:43,958
(Tatsumi) Looking back at past game records before a match is⸺

195
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:45,626
This is the golden rule of shogi.

196
00:09:47,586 --> 00:09:49,589
 (Torataro) Activity record of the Faculty of Science?

197
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:51,882
- (Tatsumi) There it is! - (Torataro) Huh?

198
00:09:54,176 --> 00:09:55,511
Ah!

199
00:09:57,138 --> 00:09:58,806
There will be no reconciliation

200
00:10:00,766 --> 00:10:02,226
I absolutely don't like it

201
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:05,688
No... no... but if you fight it in court⸺

202
00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:10,026
There is a possibility that you will have to pay the full amount of 100 million yen.

203
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:12,486
(Rie) Mr. Seyama

204
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:15,740
Write “100% admission of fault” here⸺

205
00:10:15,823 --> 00:10:17,074
I also bow to Professor Kurashiki⸺

206
00:10:17,158 --> 00:10:20,911
I think it's a smart way to keep it all together.

207
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:29,545
Is it really 100% my fault?

208
00:10:30,463 --> 00:10:31,297
Huh?

209
00:10:33,716 --> 00:10:38,596
(Tatsumi) Mr. Seyama, there's something you haven't told us, right?

210
00:10:49,732 --> 00:10:51,817
Mr. Seyama 18 years ago⸺

211
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:55,571
You graduated from the Faculty of Science at Eio University.

212
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:58,658
Moreover, that laboratory is⸺

213
00:10:58,741 --> 00:11:00,368
At the time, he was still an assistant professor.

214
00:11:01,077 --> 00:11:04,288
It was the laboratory of the plaintiff, Professor Kurashiki.

215
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:08,626
(Kurashiki) I wonder if that would be better for Seyama-kun?

216
00:11:08,709 --> 00:11:10,961
(Tatsumi) Professor Kurashiki is talking about you⸺

217
00:11:11,545 --> 00:11:15,424
He used to call me juniors and students.

218
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:19,553
By any chance... you too⸺

219
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:22,098
Weren't you involved in that experiment?

220
00:11:24,725 --> 00:11:27,395
It was an experiment that started while I was still in school⸺

221
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:29,355
just a little

222
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:36,112
Why didn't you tell me first?

223
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:40,199
My presence in that laboratory has nothing to do with this trial.

224
00:11:40,282 --> 00:11:42,743
(Rie) But then... your strategy and other things will change.

225
00:11:42,827 --> 00:11:46,038
Sorry, I have work to do.

226
00:11:47,206 --> 00:11:48,666
Excuse me

227
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:55,715
(Sound of door opening and closing)

228
00:11:58,008 --> 00:11:59,510
(Tatsuo) Isn't that bad?

229
00:12:00,094 --> 00:12:01,971
 (Kasumi) Tatsuo-san, did you hate chestnuts?

230
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:03,722
No, it's not that.

231
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:07,560
Why is the director even at our dinner table?

232
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:12,189
I don't really understand why either.

233
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:14,108
I heard from Rie-san at the agency.

234
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:16,735
Mr. Torataro: My father passed away and I live alone⸺

235
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:18,529
It's all about convenience store bento boxes.

236
00:12:18,612 --> 00:12:19,864
No, that's why...

237
00:12:19,947 --> 00:12:21,574
Not only that⸺

238
00:12:21,657 --> 00:12:25,494
To hear from my father his counter move at Gokigen Chuubisha⸺

239
00:12:25,578 --> 00:12:26,620
I brought you

240
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:28,831
Sorry, I don't understand what you're saying.

241
00:12:28,914 --> 00:12:31,375
Maybe “for damages⸺”

242
00:12:31,459 --> 00:12:36,589
"I want to hear the court strategy that the defendant should take," right?

243
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:38,549
No!

244
00:12:38,632 --> 00:12:41,010
That's a confusion of public and private.

245
00:12:41,594 --> 00:12:43,763
In the first place, the case that the lawyer is dealing with⸺

246
00:12:43,846 --> 00:12:45,806
Even with family members, don't talk recklessly.

247
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:48,476
What about lawyer ethics?

248
00:12:48,559 --> 00:12:50,394
(Kasumi) It's already a ruler!

249
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:52,563
In that case, a senior member of the judiciary⸺

250
00:12:52,646 --> 00:12:56,192
