251
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:57,234
...That's right!

252
00:12:57,318 --> 00:13:00,696
I also appreciate the general comments from my judicial seniors⸺

253
00:13:00,779 --> 00:13:01,739
I would love to hear from you.

254
00:13:01,822 --> 00:13:04,033
-(Tatsuo) Huh? -(Tatsumi) I can't wait.

255
00:13:09,914 --> 00:13:12,833
(Tatsuo) Hmm, the defendant is indeed⸺

256
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:17,713
I'm curious that you were in the plaintiff's laboratory before.

257
00:13:17,797 --> 00:13:20,716
There are no extenuating circumstances in civil court.

258
00:13:20,799 --> 00:13:25,638
In other words, the relationship between the plaintiff's professor and laboratory and the defendant is...

259
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:28,766
Does that mean it's a waste to consider it?

260
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:31,477
It's a shame

261
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:35,940
Breaking through this situation where the defendant refuses to settle the case⸺

262
00:13:36,023 --> 00:13:39,401
I thought it would be an effective way to revive myself...

263
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:45,074
Ah, I don't know if it will be a rebirth though⸺

264
00:13:45,699 --> 00:13:48,285
Isn't there a way to seek compensation for negligence?

265
00:13:48,911 --> 00:13:51,330
Negligence offset...

266
00:13:52,081 --> 00:13:53,749
(Reiko) Really 100%⸺

267
00:13:53,832 --> 00:13:55,876
Is it just my fault?

268
00:13:56,544 --> 00:13:59,171
Because the defendant, Mr. Seyama, pulled out the plug⸺

269
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:02,132
We cannot deny the fact that an important experiment was ruined.

270
00:14:02,216 --> 00:14:04,385
...But also on the laboratory side⸺

271
00:14:04,468 --> 00:14:07,179
If you can prove that there was some kind of fault...

272
00:14:07,263 --> 00:14:10,432
(Torataro) Certainly, if we can reduce the responsibility ratio⸺

273
00:14:10,516 --> 00:14:12,351
We may be able to lower your compensation!

274
00:14:12,434 --> 00:14:15,020
I need to find out more about Professor Kurashiki and his laboratory.

275
00:14:15,938 --> 00:14:16,939
let's go back to the office

276
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:19,608
(Torataro) Huh? Oh wait... now? Wait... ah...

277
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:20,526
excuse me!

278
00:14:20,609 --> 00:14:22,194
(Kasumi) Oh my, I'm so passionate about my work.

279
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:23,112
Be careful~

280
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:24,989
(Torataro) Thank you for interrupting me~

281
