Weren't you holding hands just now?

282
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:30,995
(Torataro) Um... I'm sorry.

283
00:14:31,912 --> 00:14:34,331
I would like to know more about the Kurashiki Laboratory.

284
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:39,169
I can't talk about the court case.

285
00:14:39,253 --> 00:14:40,170
Ah...

286
00:14:40,254 --> 00:14:41,714
(Tatsumi) Professor Kurashiki's⸺

287
00:14:41,797 --> 00:14:43,966
I would like to ask about your reputation.

288
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:46,093
(Student) It's not strict about attendance, so it might be popular.

289
00:14:46,176 --> 00:14:48,178
(Student) Yeah, it seems pretty cool.

290
00:14:48,262 --> 00:14:49,263
-(Student) I understand-(Student) Yeah.

291
00:14:49,346 --> 00:14:51,557
- (Torataro) I'm back now - (Rie) Good job.

292
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:52,474
I'm back now

293
00:14:52,558 --> 00:14:54,310
I found something interesting.

294
00:14:54,393 --> 00:14:56,312
(Torataro) Huh? No, this⸺

295
00:14:56,395 --> 00:14:59,064
Isn't that the Kurashiki laboratory video I saw earlier?

296
00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:01,025
(Rie) If you look closely, Mr. Seyama has pulled it out⸺

297
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:03,110
I can see the power plug

298
00:15:03,193 --> 00:15:06,864
-(Torataro) Huh? -(Rie) If you enlarge this...

299
00:15:06,947 --> 00:15:12,286
(Torataro) “Do not unplug the warmer while it is in use”

300
00:15:12,786 --> 00:15:15,956
However, the text is too thin and difficult to read.

301
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:19,335
(Rie) The location is also quite far from the power plug.

302
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:21,879
Don't pull the plug on an important experiment⸺

303
00:15:21,962 --> 00:15:24,298
The laboratory should be alert⸺

304
00:15:24,381 --> 00:15:27,843
It might be evidence that you were neglecting it.

305
00:15:27,927 --> 00:15:30,929
Now that I think about it, Mr. Seyama said that

306
00:15:31,013 --> 00:15:32,765
(Reiko) The outlet I usually use is⸺

307
00:15:32,848 --> 00:15:34,141
It's blocked

308
00:15:34,224 --> 00:15:36,310
I knew there would be cleaning involved⸺

309
00:15:36,393 --> 00:15:39,813
The fact that I didn't leave that many electrical outlets open

310
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:41,357
It's probably the laboratory's fault.

311
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:44,610
Oh, and my assistant asked me to finish cleaning quickly⸺

312
00:15:44,693 --> 00:15:46,070
He also said he felt rushed.

313
00:15:46,654 --> 00:15:50,282
Of course, that can also lead to negligence!

314
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,661
I found a workable solution

315
00:15:55,955 --> 00:15:58,874
(Judge) What is the purpose of the proof in Exhibit B No. 41?

316
00:15:58,957 --> 00:16:00,125
(Torataro) Yes.

317
00:16:01,543 --> 00:16:05,464
Exhibit No. 41 is a PR video of Eio University.

318
00:16:05,547 --> 00:16:08,550
Because this shows the inside of the laboratory⸺

319
00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:12,262
In the laboratory managed by the plaintiff⸺

320
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:13,555
The power plug of the warming device is

321
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:15,808
Neglecting to take measures to avoid being exploited⸺

322
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:19,603
We plan to prove that there was a corresponding amount of negligence.

323
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:21,730
The first player chooses a rook⸺

324
00:16:21,814 --> 00:16:26,235
After opening a corner for each other, the second player changed from 54 steps to 52 rooks.

325
00:16:26,318 --> 00:16:27,986
Select Gokigen Chuubisha

326
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:33,242
(Judge) So, what is the purpose of the proof in Exhibit A No. 34 and Exhibit A No. 35?

327
00:16:33,325 --> 00:16:37,037
First, Exhibit A No. 34 was filed by the defendant 18 years ago⸺

328
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:41,959
This is a student record of students enrolled in the Department of Biology, Faculty of Science, Eio University.

329
00:16:42,042 --> 00:16:45,004
Why such information now?

330
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:47,256
Maybe I'll try something

331
00:16:47,339 --> 00:16:51,927
(Yamaoka) The defendant has knowledge of culture experiments using heat-retaining devices.

332
00:16:52,010 --> 00:16:55,931
Even if there is no sticker, if you unplug the plug unnecessarily...

333
00:16:56,014 --> 00:16:57,266
Hey? Research results⸺

334
00:16:57,349 --> 00:17:00,477
He should have been able to foresee the risk of causing major damage.

335
00:17:00,561 --> 00:17:03,814
This is evidence showing the seriousness of the culpability.

336
00:17:03,897 --> 00:17:06,483
Next, Exhibit A No. 35 is⸺

337
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:10,446
It was being conducted right next to the plaintiff's laboratory⸺

338
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:12,990
This is a recorded video of another experiment.

339
00:17:13,073 --> 00:17:14,450
Is this evidence unrelated to this case?

340
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:17,077
(Yamaoka) Judge: To explain the purpose of proof⸺

341
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:19,705
Is it okay if I play the video here?

342
00:17:20,289 --> 00:17:21,707
(Judge) I agree.

343
00:17:25,461 --> 00:17:28,672
It's bad, it feels like they're attacking me from the other side.

344
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:31,633
First move, 7 moves, 5 eight golds, right

345
00:17:32,843 --> 00:17:34,970
Ah, is it really a sudden battle?

346
00:17:36,263 --> 00:17:37,848
Chokyu... What?

347
00:17:37,931 --> 00:17:42,478
The fastest and strongest guide to counter Gokigen Chuubisha on the back.

348
00:17:43,353 --> 00:17:47,357
We should have been cautious as the plaintiff was hoping for an early settlement.

349
00:17:47,441 --> 00:17:50,027
(Yamaoka) This experiment was conducted in the fourth week of August.

350
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:54,239
I was videotaping plants for long periods of time to observe them.

351
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:56,283
Play please

352
00:17:56,366 --> 00:17:59,912
The time code is August 20th 13:20

353
00:17:59,995 --> 00:18:02,831
This is the time the defendant pulled out the power plug.

354
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:05,084
Pay attention to the plant background

355
00:18:12,841 --> 00:18:14,009
(Tatsumi) This proof is⸺

356
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:17,221
5 Gokatsura hits right in front of the middle rook.

357
00:18:18,555 --> 00:18:21,642
5 Gokatsura's Uke is 6 2 balls is the best move

358
00:18:22,142 --> 00:18:23,352
endure

359
00:18:37,199 --> 00:18:39,576
(Ruttering) (Torataro) Ah, I pulled it out.

360
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:46,500
The hand that Mr. Seyama himself pointed to was 54 silver.

361
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:50,712
(sound of unplugging)

362
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:53,924
(Yamaoka) This video shows that the defendant is acting on his own will⸺

363
00:18:54,007 --> 00:18:56,468
It is clear that the power was intentionally unplugged⸺

364
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:59,304
The defendant's arguments regarding the negligence of the plaintiff and the laboratory are:

365
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:03,433
That means it doesn't make any sense at all.

366
00:19:03,517 --> 00:19:07,688
This is a very bad situation

367
00:19:07,771 --> 00:19:13,777
The defendant's move seems to have been one of the worst.

368
00:19:16,363 --> 00:19:18,323
Let's get straight to the point

369
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:21,118
Why did you unplug yourself?

370
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:24,413
I don't remember very well

371
00:19:24,496 --> 00:19:25,581
(Yamaoka) Yeah?

372
00:19:25,664 --> 00:19:28,333
If you were enrolled in a laboratory⸺

373
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:30,794
I should have known what would happen if I pulled the plug.

374
00:19:30,878 --> 00:19:33,172
I intentionally unplugged the power.

375
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:36,383
Isn't it because there was a grudge in the lab?

376
00:19:36,466 --> 00:19:37,676
That's not true

377
00:19:37,759 --> 00:19:43,390
(Yamaoka) Did you hold a grudge against Professor Kurashiki because your dream of becoming a researcher did not come true?

378
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:45,809
home

379
00:19:47,060 --> 00:19:49,730
I respected him as a researcher.

380
00:19:52,149 --> 00:19:54,860
-(Reiko) And I... -(Yamaoka) Yeah, what about you?

381
00:20:03,076 --> 00:20:07,956
I have been in a relationship with Professor Kurashiki for the past 18 years.

382
00:20:14,796 --> 00:20:18,926
(Reiko) But he lied to me and said he would break up with his wife and get married.

383
00:20:19,009 --> 00:20:20,260
Continue the relationship⸺

384
00:20:20,344 --> 00:20:23,555
He said he had no money to spend his own money on research.

385
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:25,849
Make me pay for the meals and hotel bill...

386
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:27,059
(Yamaoka) Enough already.

387
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:29,061
That's all for cross-examination.

388
00:20:31,688 --> 00:20:34,691
(sound of falling pieces)

389
00:20:38,612 --> 00:20:40,989
Is that testimony true?

390
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:42,741
As I said

391
00:20:43,742 --> 00:20:47,829
Are you saying that you pulled the plug because you were angry at him for continuing the affair?

392
00:20:47,913 --> 00:20:52,125
Sorry, I have work to do later.

393
00:20:57,297 --> 00:20:59,549
Why did you pull the plug?

394
00:21:00,717 --> 00:21:05,430
We can't continue this game unless we hear the reason.

395
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:12,270
I just couldn't forgive

396
00:21:14,022 --> 00:21:15,649
Excuse me

397
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:40,549
(Tatsumi) On the verge of jamming

398
00:21:50,517 --> 00:21:51,685
Ah...

399
00:21:56,732 --> 00:21:59,026
(Torataro) It's completely broken.

400
00:21:59,109 --> 00:22:00,944
There's nothing wrong with that.

401
00:22:01,028 --> 00:22:02,320
Tired of the quagmire of infidelity⸺

402
00:22:02,404 --> 00:22:05,949
A woman's mentality is to ruin the other man's research⸺

403
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:08,577
The one who understands this, Ryumi-sensei, is ten years early.

404
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:11,329
But I intentionally pulled the plug because of an affair⸺

405
00:22:11,413 --> 00:22:13,540
If the experiment fails⸺

406
00:22:13,623 --> 00:22:15,792
Negligence offset is not enough.

407
00:22:15,876 --> 00:22:17,336
Hey…

408
00:22:20,589 --> 00:22:23,175
(Rie) Are you okay? Yeah? Would you like to eat something sweet?

409
00:22:23,258 --> 00:22:24,509
(Torataro) Ah...

410
00:22:24,593 --> 00:22:26,011
I saw it

411
00:22:26,887 --> 00:22:30,432
(Rie) Huh? Ryubi-sen... Ryumi-sensei, can you see?

412
00:22:30,515 --> 00:22:35,312
(Tatsumi) There's only one move I can make now that the offset of negligence is no longer valid.

413
00:22:36,605 --> 00:22:38,648
- (Tatsumi) It's a desperate move - (Torataro) Huh?

414
00:22:48,742 --> 00:22:50,994
This is a complaint, I just wrote it.

415
00:22:51,078 --> 00:22:52,162
Huh?

416
00:22:55,832 --> 00:22:57,584
The plaintiff is Mr. Seyama

417
00:22:58,335 --> 00:23:00,212
The defendant...

418
00:23:00,295 --> 00:23:01,505
Professor Kurashiki!?

419
00:23:01,588 --> 00:23:03,131
(Rie) Huh? This is new⸺

420
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:05,008
File another lawsuit⸺

421
00:23:05,092 --> 00:23:07,177
Do you mean to sue the plaintiff?

422
00:23:07,719 --> 00:23:10,013
And the same claim for damages.

423
00:23:10,097 --> 00:23:11,598
Huh? why?

424
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:22,776
(Tatsumi) A sacrificial move is equivalent to Jishogi.

425
00:23:23,443 --> 00:23:24,736
It's shogi after all

426
00:23:24,820 --> 00:23:26,613
(Tatsumi) Rarely in a shogi match⸺

427
00:23:26,696 --> 00:23:29,783
The ball may penetrate deep into enemy territory.

428
00:23:29,866 --> 00:23:32,994
This state is called Nyugyoku.

429
00:23:34,746 --> 00:23:37,666
That each other's balls land⸺

430
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:40,585
My name is Ainyu Gyoku.

431
00:23:40,669 --> 00:23:43,422
In that case, it will be difficult to settle the matter⸺

432
00:23:43,505 --> 00:23:45,423
Declare your shogi ⸺

433
00:23:45,507 --> 00:23:50,387
Convert the pieces each person has into points and compete for the total points.

434
00:23:57,769 --> 00:23:58,770
(Rie) King has 0 points

435
00:23:58,854 --> 00:24:01,148
Rook and horn are 5 points and other 1 point

436
00:24:01,231 --> 00:24:04,526
But what about comparing the total points when claiming compensation?

437
00:24:04,609 --> 00:24:08,989
(Tatsumi) In short, with Professor Kurashiki who ruined an experiment that took 18 years.

438
00:24:09,072 --> 00:24:12,909
Mr. Seyama's life was ruined by an affair for 18 years.

439
00:24:12,993 --> 00:24:15,745
Compare which one got the most damage⸺

440
00:24:15,829 --> 00:24:18,123
The one with more damage wins

441
00:24:18,206 --> 00:24:21,626
That is the chess player in this trial.

442
00:24:21,710 --> 00:24:24,588
...If that's the case, Mr. Seyama and Professor Kurashiki are...

443
00:24:24,671 --> 00:24:28,133
I need to find out what kind of relationship they had for 18 years.

444
00:24:28,216 --> 00:24:30,677
(Rie) Ahh... University officials and people around Mr. Seyama too⸺

445
00:24:30,760 --> 00:24:32,721
I'm going to make a list of people I can talk to.

446
00:24:32,804 --> 00:24:34,723
-(Torataro) Please-(Tatsumi) Please

447
00:24:38,101 --> 00:24:40,854
(Torataro) Gyakudama? Professor Kurashiki?

448
00:24:40,937 --> 00:24:44,191
(Female) My wife's father is the president of Eio University.

449
00:24:44,274 --> 00:24:45,692
(Female) Mr. Kurashiki was able to become a professor⸺

450
00:24:45,775 --> 00:24:48,445
It's a proprietary rumor that it's because of that.

451
00:24:48,528 --> 00:24:52,407
It's hard to believe that Professor Kurashiki, who has a bad attitude, would divorce his wife...

452
00:24:52,490 --> 00:24:55,744
(Female) There's no way you can do that. You'll get fired from university.

453
00:24:55,827 --> 00:24:58,788
It seems like your wife is holding the purse strings tightly.

454
00:24:58,872 --> 00:25:00,040
yes

455
00:25:00,832 --> 00:25:03,460
After all, it's a lie that I'm breaking up with my wife⸺

456
00:25:03,543 --> 00:25:04,836
He reportedly paid for the date⸺

457
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:07,464
This is consistent with Mr. Seyama's story.

458
00:25:10,550 --> 00:25:12,135
- (Torataro) Thank you - (Nakamura) No, yes.

459
00:25:12,219 --> 00:25:15,138
You look so cute, Seyama-san.

460
00:25:15,222 --> 00:25:17,599
(Nakamura) I was planning to stay at the clinic.

461
00:25:17,682 --> 00:25:20,685
I quit university because I was worried about what others thought of me.

462
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:23,813
Mr. Seyama: Did you intend to become a researcher?

463
00:25:23,897 --> 00:25:26,399
He was the best in his class.

464
00:25:28,068 --> 00:25:32,739
Actually, I wanted to work in research.

465
00:25:34,574 --> 00:25:40,413
Mr. Seyama conducted an experiment on slime mold in that laboratory⸺

466
00:25:40,497 --> 00:25:42,874
What on earth were you thinking when you saw it?

467
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:46,211
-(Tatsumi) I'm back now.-(Rie) Good job.

468
00:25:46,294 --> 00:25:48,505
Hey, isn't this something strange?

469
00:25:48,588 --> 00:25:49,548
Huh?

470
00:25:51,549 --> 00:25:54,553
Is this the evidence presented by the plaintiff?

471
00:25:54,636 --> 00:25:56,429
-(Torataro) Example slime mold data-(Rie) Yeah.

472
00:25:56,513 --> 00:25:59,057
I have been collecting data every day for 18 years without fail.

473
00:25:59,140 --> 00:26:00,809
This is something to prove⸺

474
00:26:00,892 --> 00:26:03,770
Isn't it weird when you compare July and August?

475
00:26:04,354 --> 00:26:08,233
(Tatsumi) For July, the times and numbers are carefully written⸺

476
00:26:08,316 --> 00:26:11,653
It's true that my handwriting has been rough since August 2nd.

477
00:26:11,736 --> 00:26:14,739
(Torataro) I feel like I've suddenly lost my motivation.

478
00:26:15,323 --> 00:26:20,036
(phone ringtone)

479
00:26:21,037 --> 00:26:24,749
Yes, this is Ayuda Law Office, from super quick battles to shogi.

480
00:26:28,336 --> 00:26:31,756
Ah... An application for consultation outside of litigation?

481
00:26:32,382 --> 00:26:34,801
Tomorrow at 10:00 Yes, I understand.

482
00:26:34,884 --> 00:26:36,511
Excuse me

483
00:26:38,054 --> 00:26:40,015
I did it, the other person also got on board.

484
00:26:40,598 --> 00:26:45,520
It's finally time to calculate the score for Mochi Shogi.

485
00:26:47,022 --> 00:26:49,858
(Torataro) As much as I can remember from Mr. Seyama himself⸺

486
00:26:49,941 --> 00:26:54,821
I was sent a list of what I paid for meals and entertainment expenses...

487
00:26:54,904 --> 00:26:56,656
(Rie) Hmm, well, just in case⸺

488
00:26:56,740 --> 00:26:59,826
100,000 yen per month for meals and hotel expenses⸺

489
00:26:59,909 --> 00:27:03,288
times 12 times 18 years

490
00:27:04,080 --> 00:27:05,582
Just over 20 million

491
00:27:06,625 --> 00:27:09,336
Even if you factor in the alimony, it's not even close to 100 million yen.

492
00:27:09,419 --> 00:27:13,214
(Torataro) If things continue like this, I'll have to pay the difference.

493
00:27:14,507 --> 00:27:17,385
(Rie) If you want to end the affair in the first place⸺

494
00:27:17,469 --> 00:27:20,930
They should have asked the professor for damages from the beginning.

495
00:27:21,014 --> 00:27:24,851
I wonder why I bother pulling out the plug...

496
00:27:24,934 --> 00:27:27,645
I just couldn't forgive

497
00:27:28,855 --> 00:27:30,648
If it's not about adultery...

498
00:27:33,401 --> 00:27:35,820
I will hear from Mr. Seyama again.

499
00:27:35,904 --> 00:27:37,322
(Torataro) Huh? Oh wait...

500
00:27:40,575 --> 00:27:43,620
(Reiko) There's nothing else I can tell you...

501
00:27:44,829 --> 00:27:48,708
I took this case to win this case.

502
00:27:49,918 --> 00:27:51,753
Even if I lose⸺

503
00:27:52,462 --> 00:27:55,673
I can't give up without being satisfied

504
00:27:56,383 --> 00:28:01,388
Despite appearances, you're persistent.

505
00:28:04,432 --> 00:28:09,312
When I asked him why he pulled the plug, Mr. Seyama

506
00:28:09,813 --> 00:28:12,315
You said, “I just couldn’t forgive you.”

507
00:28:12,399 --> 00:28:14,651
So that just happened...

508
00:28:14,734 --> 00:28:19,072
(Tatsumi) About Professor Kurashiki who cheated on me and had an affair for 18 years⸺

509
00:28:19,155 --> 00:28:21,658
I couldn't forgive it, so I pulled the plug.

510
00:28:23,118 --> 00:28:27,789
But I just can't accept that.

511
00:28:33,253 --> 00:28:34,546
Why do you think so?

512
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:40,468
When I saw this room, I understood.

513
00:28:40,552 --> 00:28:46,224
Mr. Seyama says he hasn't lost his passion for research.

514
00:28:55,358 --> 00:28:59,446
I started playing shogi at the age of 5⸺

515
00:28:59,529 --> 00:29:04,742
I was immersed in shogi every day until I left the encouragement group at the age of 23.

516
00:29:06,453 --> 00:29:08,830
For 18 years

517
00:29:10,331 --> 00:29:12,417
That's why I don't really understand

518
00:29:13,209 --> 00:29:18,131
The research that Mr. Seyama has cherished for 18 years⸺

519
00:29:18,214 --> 00:29:23,052
To feel so unforgivable that I want it to end...

520
00:29:23,136 --> 00:29:29,184
There must have been something more than just an affair, right?

521
00:29:36,149 --> 00:29:37,984
(Reiko) Hey, can I ask you something?

522
00:29:40,612 --> 00:29:44,032
When I stopped playing shogi, which I had dedicated my life to for 18 years⸺

523
00:29:45,992 --> 00:29:47,744
How did you feel?

524
00:30:08,139 --> 00:30:10,141
Honestly, I don't remember very well.

525
00:30:13,019 --> 00:30:19,567
But I haven't stopped playing shogi or given up on it.

526
00:30:20,527 --> 00:30:24,823
Even if we leave, shogi will always be within me.

527
00:30:26,741 --> 00:30:28,076
What can I say...

528
00:30:31,913 --> 00:30:35,041
Maybe I just changed the way I interacted with shogi.

529
00:30:44,133 --> 00:30:45,176
yes

530
00:31:03,903 --> 00:31:05,989
I didn't want to show it, but...

531
00:31:14,289 --> 00:31:15,582
This is...

532
00:31:39,647 --> 00:31:41,190
(Student) Huh? Huh? look look

533
00:31:41,274 --> 00:31:43,067
(Student) What? Graduation ceremony?

534
00:31:43,151 --> 00:31:46,404
(Rie) Even when playing shogi in an off-field battle, it's a competition uniform.

535
00:31:46,487 --> 00:31:47,905
You wear it properly

536
00:31:47,989 --> 00:31:48,990
(Student) Hakama? Huh?

537
00:31:49,574 --> 00:31:52,952
(Yamaoka) In other words, compare the compensation amounts in the two lawsuits⸺

538
00:31:53,036 --> 00:31:56,289
The condition of the settlement is that you pay the difference.

539
00:31:56,372 --> 00:32:00,793
The one with the highest total score of the pieces is the winner of Shogi.

540
00:32:00,877 --> 00:32:02,921
I think it will probably never get through.

541
00:32:03,004 --> 00:32:07,592
Normally, I would not be able to accept a proposal like this at all.

542
00:32:07,675 --> 00:32:11,387
Based on the request of the client, we decided to comply with this request as well.

543
00:32:12,472 --> 00:32:13,890
(Rie) Start here

544
00:32:13,973 --> 00:32:15,016
Eh, Mr. Seyama⸺

545
00:32:15,099 --> 00:32:19,228
I believed Professor Kurashiki's lie that he would break up with his wife and remarry⸺

546
00:32:19,312 --> 00:32:21,564
Continued an affair for 18 years⸺

547
00:32:21,648 --> 00:32:26,110
Mr. Seyama paid most of the entertainment expenses during that time.

548
00:32:26,194 --> 00:32:29,489
(Torataro) This is Mr. Seyama's credit card statement history.

549
00:32:29,572 --> 00:32:32,075
Comparing this with the message, this is the expenditure.

550
00:32:32,158 --> 00:32:35,119
The money was paid for Professor Kurashiki...

551
00:32:44,170 --> 00:32:46,714
(Tatsumi) A long game of over 400 moves

552
00:32:46,798 --> 00:32:49,384
Both players' balls enter the enemy's territory⸺

553
00:32:49,467 --> 00:32:51,928
I can't find a hand anymore

554
00:32:52,595 --> 00:32:55,932
(Torataro) It is clear that the liability for compensation for those expenses is clear⸺

555
00:32:56,015 --> 00:32:57,183
Mr. Seyama due to infidelity.

556
00:32:57,266 --> 00:33:00,603
Including the reason why I gave up my career as a researcher⸺

557
00:33:00,687 --> 00:33:05,983
I will demand compensation for this amount, including compensation.

558
00:33:12,281 --> 00:33:14,534
(Kurashiki) 31 million?

559
00:33:14,617 --> 00:33:16,369
It's off topic.

560
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:21,791
Professor Kurashiki had 18 years of research ruined.

561
00:33:21,874 --> 00:33:23,584
If you bring up mental pain⸺

562
00:33:23,668 --> 00:33:26,337
This one will be much bigger!

563
00:33:26,963 --> 00:33:28,047
(Tatsumi) At this point⸺

564
00:33:28,131 --> 00:33:30,717
95 feet and 17 gold are likely to be taken⸺

565
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:33,386
It is a difficult situation to surpass in points

566
00:33:33,469 --> 00:33:34,846
But...

567
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:38,683
I will submit additional evidence regarding that research.

568
00:33:39,267 --> 00:33:41,936
American Strand Research Center⸺

569
00:33:42,019 --> 00:33:44,355
This is a report published online.

570
00:33:45,606 --> 00:33:47,608
(Torataro) Translations are also available.

571
00:33:50,111 --> 00:33:52,238
(Reiko) I didn't want to show it, but...

572
00:33:55,032 --> 00:33:56,242
(Rong Mei) 5 triangles form…

573
00:33:58,953 --> 00:34:02,957
Mr. Seyama, who has been monitoring the research for 18 years⸺

574
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:07,587
I found this while looking into research data on slime molds from around the world.

575
00:34:07,670 --> 00:34:11,215
The center was created by Professor Kurashiki.

576
00:34:11,299 --> 00:34:13,259
For the practical application of similar antibiotics⸺

577
00:34:13,342 --> 00:34:16,012
It says that it is likely to be successful

578
00:34:16,095 --> 00:34:20,433
The company plans to obtain a patent as soon as the antibiotic's effectiveness is recognized.

579
00:34:20,516 --> 00:34:22,643
(Tatsumi) This is not an officially published paper⸺

580
00:34:22,727 --> 00:34:24,604
Not released in Japan

581
00:34:24,687 --> 00:34:28,441
But what if this was announced?

582
00:34:28,524 --> 00:34:34,072
The research you spent 18 years on will be meaningless.

583
00:34:35,156 --> 00:34:38,576
That's why I wanted the first trial to end quickly⸺

584
00:34:38,659 --> 00:34:41,162
So you started negotiating for a settlement early on?

585
00:34:43,998 --> 00:34:46,501
...However, this claim is not for lost profits⸺

586
00:34:46,584 --> 00:34:48,836
This is just the actual loss for research costs...

587
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:52,006
(Torataro) That research has produced no results⸺

588
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:54,217
Since it turned out to be meaningless⸺

589
00:34:54,300 --> 00:34:58,012
We request a significant reduction in your bill.

590
00:34:58,096 --> 00:35:00,223
(Rie) By the way, in other laboratories in the Faculty of Science⸺

591
00:35:00,306 --> 00:35:04,852
Here's the average amount for a single experiment.

592
00:35:08,898 --> 00:35:11,234
(Yamaoka) 23 million yen?

593
00:35:14,445 --> 00:35:15,947
(Tatsumi) I declare

594
00:35:16,030 --> 00:35:19,283
The total score of this piece is 31 points.

595
00:35:19,367 --> 00:35:21,786
Opponent's score: 23 points

596
00:35:21,869 --> 00:35:24,914
Result: I won at Mochi Shogi

597
00:35:25,706 --> 00:35:27,333
Pay the difference of 8 million yen⸺

598
00:35:27,416 --> 00:35:29,377
If you could withdraw the first complaint⸺

599
00:35:29,460 --> 00:35:33,464
This side will also drop the lawsuit and agree to a settlement.

600
00:35:36,801 --> 00:35:37,885
Huh?

601
00:35:46,894 --> 00:35:48,271
Are you satisfied?

602
00:35:49,188 --> 00:35:50,857
As my researcher⸺

603
00:35:50,940 --> 00:35:53,734
Ruined my life as a professor⸺

604
00:35:54,902 --> 00:35:57,196
Is that enough for you?

605
00:36:00,032 --> 00:36:01,993
18 years⸺

606
00:36:05,037 --> 00:36:06,914
thank you

607
00:36:15,923 --> 00:36:17,800
Huh... (sound of door closing)

608
00:36:23,723 --> 00:36:27,310
(Reiko) I met that person when I was 20 years old.

609
00:36:28,853 --> 00:36:30,730
Two years after we started dating⸺

610
00:36:31,731 --> 00:36:36,819
He was asked to marry the school president's daughter.

611
00:36:38,487 --> 00:36:42,825
I believe in Kurashiki's talent as a researcher⸺

612
00:36:43,367 --> 00:36:46,370
I was prepared to withdraw from myself⸺

613
00:36:47,788 --> 00:36:50,416
In the end, they end up having an affair...

614
00:36:54,003 --> 00:36:58,549
A new future will definitely come where these children will be useful.

615
00:37:01,427 --> 00:37:03,137
it's our child

616
00:37:05,222 --> 00:37:07,266
(Reiko) Just that experiment⸺

617
00:37:07,350 --> 00:37:12,230
It was the only proof that connected me to that place.

618
00:37:13,689 --> 00:37:18,611
So why don't you do the cleaning work in the laboratory yourself?

619
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:20,529
Yeah

620
00:37:21,530 --> 00:37:26,619
I could see that experiment moving forward in time...

621
00:37:27,119 --> 00:37:28,287
good morning

622
00:37:28,371 --> 00:37:32,375
It was one of the few things I had to live for.

623
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:37,046
But why did you do it yourself?

624
00:37:39,966 --> 00:37:44,845
Because that report was released, right?

625
00:37:47,640 --> 00:37:53,145
I found this while searching an overseas site last month.

626
00:37:53,229 --> 00:37:54,855
Let him know right away...

627
00:37:54,939 --> 00:37:57,608
It's a shame that I got ahead of myself⸺

628
00:37:57,692 --> 00:37:59,110
It's been going on for 18 years⸺

629
00:37:59,193 --> 00:38:02,113
Can't you just release the data now?

630
00:38:03,739 --> 00:38:05,366
-(Kurashiki) It's a waste.-(Reiko) Huh?

631
00:38:06,534 --> 00:38:10,871
Their experimental method is much more efficient and accurate.

632
00:38:10,955 --> 00:38:12,248
Huh? So what about those kids?

633
00:38:12,331 --> 00:38:15,626
Adabana: No academic evaluation

634
00:38:15,710 --> 00:38:19,630
(Reiko) Huh? But please cancel the current experiment⸺

635
00:38:19,714 --> 00:38:21,465
What about starting a new experiment?

636
00:38:21,549 --> 00:38:23,884
There's no way that's possible

637
00:38:23,968 --> 00:38:27,763
During this period, we “lost to overseas research institutions”

638
00:38:27,847 --> 00:38:29,932
Try saying, “It was a useless experiment.”

639
00:38:30,016 --> 00:38:31,350
Even research funds will stop coming down.

640
00:38:31,434 --> 00:38:33,477
(Reiko) If so, what are you planning to do?

641
00:38:33,561 --> 00:38:35,021
(Kurashiki) Research never ends

642
00:38:35,104 --> 00:38:37,315
There is still time until the paper is published.

643
00:38:38,774 --> 00:38:42,069
I can somehow hide it until my retirement age.

644
00:38:42,153 --> 00:38:44,030
Experiments that you know won't yield any results⸺

645
00:38:44,113 --> 00:38:45,865
Is it sane to continue for self-protection?

646
00:38:45,948 --> 00:38:47,700
(Kurashiki) I'm sure there are many other such researchers.

647
00:38:47,783 --> 00:38:49,618
Remember me

648
00:38:49,702 --> 00:38:51,245
The day I started the experiment⸺

649
00:38:51,329 --> 00:38:55,666
You envisioned a future where new antibiotics would save people.

650
00:38:55,750 --> 00:38:57,168
-(Reiko) Something new... -(Kurashiki) Hey, Reiko.

651
00:38:59,170 --> 00:39:02,465
I'm not old enough to dream about the future anymore.

652
00:39:04,425 --> 00:39:06,052
(Reiko) That moment⸺

653
00:39:07,678 --> 00:39:10,681
I felt like I woke up from a long dream

654
00:39:11,932 --> 00:39:13,934
So what about the power plug?

655
00:39:15,061 --> 00:39:16,771
In the laboratory⸺

656
00:39:17,855 --> 00:39:20,941
Time continues to pass without any change from before⸺

657
00:39:21,025 --> 00:39:23,277
Look at that warming device⸺

658
00:39:24,695 --> 00:39:29,367
There is no new future, and nothing is being created⸺

659
00:39:29,450 --> 00:39:34,413
It's just there for the research money and the professorship position⸺

660
00:39:35,664 --> 00:39:37,625
I just can't forgive...

661
00:39:55,267 --> 00:39:58,145
We apologize for any inconvenience caused⸺

662
00:39:59,146 --> 00:40:01,774
Thank you very much

663
00:40:12,159 --> 00:40:13,744
Mr. Seyama

664
00:40:16,872 --> 00:40:19,416
What will you do now?

665
00:40:22,378 --> 00:40:24,046
What should I do?

666
00:40:30,803 --> 00:40:35,683
When you finish something, you have to start anew.

667
00:40:37,393 --> 00:40:39,895
The next 18 years⸺

668
00:40:40,646 --> 00:40:45,025
Focus on winning like Ryumi-sensei

669
00:40:48,028 --> 00:40:50,072
I'll definitely win

670
00:40:51,991 --> 00:40:53,993
♪～

671
00:41:09,133 --> 00:41:11,594
(Torataro) Another impression battle

672
00:41:12,803 --> 00:41:15,472
Moreover, in Ryumi-sensei's room.

673
00:41:15,556 --> 00:41:19,351
(Tatsumi) It was a game where I learned a lot.

674
00:41:22,646 --> 00:41:25,024
Thanks to you, I understood it myself.

675
00:41:26,692 --> 00:41:27,568
What?

676
00:41:27,651 --> 00:41:30,196
Shogi pieces do not betray the mover.

677
00:41:30,779 --> 00:41:34,909
But sometimes people betray someone's expectations⸺

678
00:41:35,451 --> 00:41:37,828
Sometimes I even tell a lie

679
00:41:39,663 --> 00:41:41,957
(Torataro) Yeah, that's right.

680
00:41:42,041 --> 00:41:43,667
(Tatsumi) That's why it's so rewarding.

681
00:41:43,751 --> 00:41:44,919
Understood

682
00:41:49,465 --> 00:41:51,842
How can we be locked in a room alone?

683
00:41:51,926 --> 00:41:53,719
It's a terrible situation...

684
00:41:55,012 --> 00:41:56,972
Is the presiding judge overhearing?

685
00:41:57,056 --> 00:41:58,182
Oh no, look

686
00:41:58,265 --> 00:42:00,059
It's Wi-Fi.

687
00:42:00,142 --> 00:42:01,518
 (Torataro) Me too, honestly⸺

688
00:42:01,602 --> 00:42:03,354
There were so many things I didn't understand.

689
00:42:03,437 --> 00:42:06,732
The feelings of a woman like Seyama-san⸺

690
00:42:07,274 --> 00:42:09,235
Love, especially

691
00:42:09,318 --> 00:42:11,237
Koigokoro…

692
00:42:15,866 --> 00:42:18,118
I have never seen such a fixed mark.

693
00:42:18,202 --> 00:42:21,038
(Torataro) Oh, that's right, Dr. Ryumi.

694
00:42:21,121 --> 00:42:23,666
It means you have never been in love...

695
00:42:24,291 --> 00:42:25,626
Ah sorry sorry sorry this⸺

696
00:42:25,709 --> 00:42:26,877
Um...it's going to become harassment.

697
00:42:26,961 --> 00:42:28,045
Those are your words⸺

698
00:42:28,128 --> 00:42:30,339
It's true that my life is 80% shogi⸺

699
00:42:30,422 --> 00:42:32,424
“Rokuho Zensho” 20%.

700
00:42:32,508 --> 00:42:36,136
Still, I only have some love experience...

701
00:42:36,220 --> 00:42:38,847
Is there a past that my father doesn't know about?

702
00:42:38,931 --> 00:42:40,641
Oh, what?

703
00:42:41,850 --> 00:42:43,352
Does that mean there is?

704
00:42:43,435 --> 00:42:45,145
～♪

705
00:42:45,229 --> 00:42:49,149
 (mobile phone vibrator)

706
00:42:49,233 --> 00:42:50,901
Rie-san?

707
00:42:51,944 --> 00:42:53,445
Yes Hello, what happened?

708
00:42:53,529 --> 00:42:55,656
It's tough! I got a new request...

709
00:42:55,739 --> 00:42:57,700
Please wait a moment, Ryuumi-sensei is also here.

710
00:42:57,783 --> 00:42:58,742
It's a new request (mobile phone tap sound)

711
00:43:00,160 --> 00:43:01,745
It's a trial.

712
00:43:01,829 --> 00:43:02,997
Are you the first mover? Are you on the back foot?

713
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:03,914
(Rie)...or rather⸺

714
00:43:03,998 --> 00:43:06,208
It's a criminal trial, not a civil one.

715
00:43:06,917 --> 00:43:09,169
Moreover, there was a murder case.

716
00:43:10,629 --> 00:43:11,714
Murder incident!?

717
00:43:18,429 --> 00:43:19,930
(Tatsumi) Did you kill the victim?

718
00:43:20,014 --> 00:43:21,390
 (Mikimoto) I am innocent.

719
00:43:21,473 --> 00:43:23,350
(Torataro) He was charged with murder, right?

720
00:43:23,434 --> 00:43:24,268
 (Tatsumi) Against AI⸺

721
00:43:24,351 --> 00:43:26,228
It's like playing a game.

722
00:43:26,312 --> 00:43:28,314
“The heir has disappeared!?”

723
00:43:28,397 --> 00:43:29,857
 (Taeko) But it's unfounded.

724
00:43:29,940 --> 00:43:30,858
(Tatsumi) This is us⸺

725
00:43:30,941 --> 00:43:32,860
This is a complete guide.
